We analyzed the spatial distribution of the HBC using several geostatistical measures of dispersion, including mean centers and standard deviational ellipses (SDE). The mean centers were calculated using the average of the x and y coordinates for all the locations of HBC at the annual and monthly scale (Wright and Sen Roy 2022). The change in location of the mean centers is useful for identifying changes in spatial patterns of HBC from 2002 to 2022 (Fig. 5a, c). Given the year-to-year variations in HBC, we also calculated the SDE to determine the directional trend and variation at the annual and monthly scale by calculating the standard deviation of the x and y coordinates from the mean centers to define the axis of the ellipse (ESRI 2024a). The specific calculations for the SDE are given below:\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
